f
 f(t) = \|u + tv\|, \qquad t \in \mathbb{R}. 
 \begin{align} f(tx + (1 - t)y) & = \|u + (tx + (1-t)y) v\| \\ & = \|tu + (1 - t) u + tx v + (1 - t) y v\| \\ & = \|t(u + xv) + (1 - t)(u + yv)\| \\ & \leq \|t (u + xv)\| + \|(1 - t)(u + yv)\| \\ & = t f(x) + (1 - t) f(y) \end{align} 
